Text.CultureInvariantString:
Workers wash clothes using the washing
machines and fold clothes on tables

Behind the wire fence is a back
area for maintenance workers only.

Workers push carts through here that
are cleaned and folded.  This is also a small storage area
where workers place thingson shelves.

This is the room workers toss their dirty clothes
into shelves or laundry bins. Depending on what
type of clothes the worker is using, kitchen worker,
mechanic, etc. They are individually seperated and
then washed on type of clothing at a time.
This is where clean clothes are stored after they have been washed.

Short hallway that leads to different rooms.
Not 100% sure where the 3rd door will lead but this
area will be the 3rd layer in terms of back rooms. Kitchen area,
laundry room, shower room is the second layer. This short
 room is the 3rd layer, so make it dark and creepy
